⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of FUCK
node PHN · PHN · ⟦FUCK:PHN:a9c90e⟧

WHO   — FUCK — the first codex of PHONETIKOS
WHAT  — FUCK — old Germanic, falsely acronymed, grammatically the most flexible word in English, and the clearest single case of a taboo migrating from the holy to the bodily.
WHERE — a Germanic root for thrust/strike, carried into English and policed for seven centuries  Framework inputs: Sheidlower's The F-Word; the OED; Paul Booth's 1310 find; the Flen flyys cipher; Mohr's Holy Sh*t  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because English needed one short, hard syllable that could be every part of speech and still be forbidden — the word that carries the modern taboo on its back.
HOW   — Cognate with Dutch fokken and German ficken; first secure in a 1310 nickname, enciphered in 1475, exiled from dictionaries until the OED's 1972 Supplement.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Seven hundred years old, Germanic to the bone, and never once an acronym.

